                <div type="edition" xml:lang="okz-Latn" rendition="class:83231 maturity:83213">
                   <p>
                      <lb n="1"/><g type="circleTarget">.</g>vraḥ śrījaya pratiṣthā<g type="circleTarget">.</g>
                   </p>
</div>
        <!--    <div type="apparatus">
                          
         </div> -->
          <div type="translation" resp="part:kuch">
             <p n="1">The deities <supplied reason="subaudible">which</supplied> Śrī Jaya has installed.</p><!-- kuch: Arlo's suggested translation: Sainte dédicace de Śrī Jaya[varman] or sainte dédicace en vue de l'illustre victoire.-->
</div> 
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>There are seven identical inscriptions, i.e. <ref target="DHARMA_INSCIK01474.xml">K. 1474</ref>, <ref target="DHARMA_INSCIK01475.xml">K. 1475</ref>, <ref target="DHARMA_INSCIK01477.xml">K. 1477</ref> through <ref target="DHARMA_INSCIK01481.xml">K. 1481</ref>.</p>
<p>The inscription is doubtful as far as term <foreign>pratiṣthā</foreign> is concerned; in its place the expression <foreign>ta go sthāpa</foreign> is expected as in many examples of inscriptions on doorjamb of temples belonging to the reign of Jayavaraman VII.</p>
         </div> 
